    Page Object Model is a design pattern.

    For each page
    in the application,
    there should be a
    corresponding page class.

    This page class will
    find the WebElements
    of that web page and
    also contains Page Methods
    which perform operations
    on those Web Elements.


    How did you implement the POM in your framework?

    I work on a Ice Mortgage Technology application.
    I have the loginPage, LandingPage, and passwordPage,
    and I also have different menu options.
    In each page class, I store the web elements
    and their actions/ methods.
    For example, in the customers Page,
    I have the elements for that specific
    page and also their actions like save & close,
    create new customer, etc. I separate all test cases from the